      "amount": "1 tbsp",
      "notes": "freshly squeezed"
    },
    {
      "name": "ground cumin",
      "amount": "1 tsp",
      "notes": "optional"
    },
    {
      "name": "fresh cilantro",
      "amount": "2 tbsp",
      "notes": "chopped, for garnish"
    }
  ],
  "instructions": [
    "Heat the olive oil in a large pot over medium heat.",
    "Add the diced onion and sauté until translucent, about 4 minutes.",
    "Stir in the minced garlic, smoked paprika, cumin, and smoked sea salt; cook for 1 minute until fragrant.",
    "Pour in the vegetable broth and bring to a gentle simmer.",
    "Reduce heat to low and stir in the labneh slowly, whisking to avoid curdling; keep the soup at a very low simmer for 8 minutes.",
    "Add lemon juice and adjust seasoning with additional salt if needed.",
    "Remove from heat and let rest for 2 minutes.",
    "Serve hot, garnished with chopped cilantro.",
    "Optionally, drizzle a little olive oil on top for extra richness."
  ],
